-- Tropical Storm Matthew Moving `Quickly' Towards Central America Countries
-- B y   M i k e   H a r r i s o n
-- 2010-09-24T06:35:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-24/tropical-storm-matthew-moving-quickly-towards-central-america-countries.html
Tropical Storm Matthew is moving
quickly westward toward Central America and is expected to be
near the Nicaragua/Honduras border later today, the National
Hurricane Center said in its latest advisory on its website.  Matthew, which could become a hurricane today, is moving
toward the west at 17 miles per hour (28 kilometers per hour)
with maximum sustained winds at 45 mph. It is currently 275
miles east of Puerto Cabezas, Nicaragua.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mike Harrison at 
 mharrison5@bloomberg.net  